<recipe>
  <name>Tortilla Pie</name>
  <safe_name>Tortilla_Pie</safe_name>
  <yield_count></yield_count>
  <yield_measure>Servings</yield_measure>
  <notes>I stood in fear of this recipe for some time, having horrible recollections about a dish involving tortillas and worrying that this one was perhaps it.  I've made it several times and under several conditions including make-ahead freezing and have not yet come up with a mystery method for fouling this thing up.  Delicious 70s goodness!

The original recipe called for a "small can of niblets" which I like for sentimental reasons but we roll with big bags of frozen kernels at our house and that works fine too.</notes>
